<br>
1 point of mental clarity will give a level 60 mage an increase in dps of 0.66 (assuming mana dam ratio of 4:1. This is for the non-SCM and non-SCF mage. These will have better ratios).<br>
<br>
FB is 0.13 increase in dps. So mental clarity I is 5 times better than FB.<br>
<br>
To compare, regen 1 is for a self-rodder aprox 0.33 FT. Or 1/3 of mental clarity. So regen 1 is still better than FB.<br>
<br>
As it is now, I suspect that they cannot increase mage dps with a singe AA with more than a few  percent. (SCM being the best of these, raising it 10 percent or so). Lets assume that VI will accept a raise in dps of 3% for this AA. lets (conservatively) assume that an epic mage has a dps of 120.<br>
<br>
3% of 120 is 3.6. (Which is around the strength of SCF III I believe). 90 mins is 5400 ekstra dammage. Divided over 36 secs that is 150 extra dps. So this is the number that should be aimed for if the FB is free of manacost, and if VI accept that an increase in dps should be part of the equation. (If it is not, I cannot see why mages should waste energy on it). <br>
<br>
This will probably get the pet killed, but hey, that would be fun =).<br>
<br>
An alternative to this is to let FB cost a lot of mana. for example 2k mana.<br>
<br>
if it costs 2k mana, they can allow it to increase its effectiveness, without disturbing the mages dps to much. For 2k mana, you can have at least 8k dammage done nuking. And it can be delivered in less than 1 min. So if you transfer it to the pet, the pet should be doing more than 8k extra dammage in the FB period, to be competitive. The above increase of 5400 damage was assuming an increase in dps of 3.6. So these two should be added if the dps increase holds. 13400 damage in 36 secs is 377 more dps per second. I doubt the pet will be unnoticed by the mob for long =). So most likely, the mob will turn around and remove the pet before the period is over. But hey, it will be great fun!<br>
<br>
Basically, the FB must either increase the dps of the mage, or give the ability to deliver a single hard blow. <br>
<br>
if it increases dps, it can either cost mana, or be manafree. <br>
<br>
The equation for the manafree overall dps increase version is as follows:<br>
<br>
  dpsIncFB = ( dpsIncPercentIntended * avgMageDps * 90 (mins) * 60 (sec) ) / durationOfFB.<br>
<br>
The manaconsuming version would be:<br>
<br>
  dpsIncFB2 = dpsIncFB + manacost * (manaDamRatioMage) / durationOfFB.<br>
<br>
<br>
The version that does not increase dps for mages is not interesting for mages I believe, so I will not bother with it.<br>
<br>
The current version of FB has dpsIncFB = 20. To small by hundreds I believe.<br>
<br>
The thing that I like about having a manacosting FB is that we can do damage with Jabober. That is what mages are about =).<br>
<br>
Iblis<br>
<br>
PS: Most AA can be converted to dps increases, I wonder why it hasn't been done on the board. Perhaps I should spend the sunday on that =). <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uiblisthemage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IblisTheMage</A> at: 9/8/02 12:27:04 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ujazzen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jazzen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 182<br> <font color=#333333>(9/8/02 12:31:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=366.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: FB math - numbers speculation - Also for Rick Waters</span><hr size=1> Very good post and some pretty good numbers. I hope that this thread isn't moved/locked/derailed by those that do not agree with directing post to Verant. Lets keep this thread on topic.  I do not know what FB needs to make it better but atm it is worthless. Something needs to be done.<br>
