<br>
Lets say I can cast 4 shock of fiery blades in 36 seconds for 115 dps.  My pet also contributes 50 dps normally.  This puts my 36 second burn dps at 165.  The only ways I can increase this are:<br>
<br>
Spellcasting Fury (Random)<br>
Spellcasting Subtlety to a limited extent.<br>
Frenzied Burnout.<br>
<br>
Not only is it one of only a few skills(of which mental clarity is not included) that can increase my max burn damage, but it stacks with all of the others.  If I had this skill now, I would actually use it.  In an xp group, it would be the skill to use when you got a bunch of unexpected adds or when you were fighting the big boss.  It might let me solo things I could not do before, and certian mobs would become easier.  <br>
<br>
I'm not saying that it couldn't be a bit more useful..  personally I would like to see either the damage output upped or have some other effect added, but despite possible wishes to the contrary Frenzied Burnout does <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> not</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> appear to ever have been intended as a long term damage boost(which mages really didn't need anyway).  Therefore it really doesn't help to analyze it as such. <br>
