<br>
I do believe that Frenzied Burnout was intended to make the pet do a lot of damage for 36 seonds than add more damage with the explosion.<br>
<br>
I never and I doubt 99% of anyone who reads these boards thought that a class ability that takes 24 aaxp points to get would only raise pet damage by 700 total damage before fading.<br>
<br>
The name alone proves that much in my opinoin.<br>
<br>
Each of out burnout lines were designed to make the pet hit faster, and do a lot more damage. The pet delay goes way down under burnout, and damage per second soars.<br>
<br>
SCF3 (Spell Casting Fury) by it self allows your nukes to crit for more than 700 extra damage, and you can get that before you get frenzied burnout, also note that Wizards and Druids both get SCF as an ability if they wish to get it, and I know a lot of wizards try for this as soon as they have manaburn. My point in bringing this up is to point out, that increasing damage via AAXP points is something Verant has in mind and is implimenting. ManaBurn/LifeBurn/DC all are aaxp skills to let players do more damage on mobs than previously possible.<br>
<br>
PLEASE DO NOT get side tracked, I mention them to show that improving damage output is part of what AAXP does, and not just for Wizards the premier nuking class but for druids and the magician class as well. This skill allows nukes to hit for more than 700 more damage on certain spells.<br>
<br>
To think that frenzied burnout was a skill added to only add less than a nuke worth of extra damage can't be right. It makes no  sense at all. 700 damage for that many aaxp points, and useable every 90 minutes doesn't make any sense.<br>
<br>
I still feel it was meant to turn out pet into a shredding machine for 36 seconds, and do a ton more damage.<br>
<br>
The way it is now, it is broken, and I think the poster of this thread is trying to show what he feels may have been what was intended but never happened. <br>
<br>
I don't know if he is right, but I hope so, because if it was intended to only do 700 more damage before wearing off than I see no point in this skill at all, it would be put in the same catergory as Mass Group Buff, not something at all useful to get.<br>
